I- Pruned Decision Tree-GINI¶

In [112]:
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier

# Decision Tree Classifier using gini, 

model=DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion='gini',random_state=1,max_depth=3,min_samples_leaf=5)
model.fit(x_train,y_train)
y_pred=model.predict(x_test)

trn_sc=model.score(x_train,y_train)
tst_sc=model.score(x_test,y_test)
rcl_sc=recall_score(y_test,y_pred)
prc_sc=precision_score(y_test,y_pred)
roc_sc=roc_auc_score(y_test,y_pred)

# Adding the values to the record
Algorithm.append('Decision Tree gini')
train.append(trn_sc)
test.append(tst_sc)
recall.append(rcl_sc)
precision.append(prc_sc)
roc.append(roc_sc)

print('trn_sc=',round(trn_sc*100,2),'%')
print('tst_sc=',round(tst_sc*100,2),'%')
print('rcl_sc=',round(rcl_sc*100,2),'%')
print('prc_sc=',round(prc_sc*100,2),'%')
print('roc_sc=',round(roc_sc*100,2),'%')

# Using confusion matrix graph to show the model's performance
cm=metrics.confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred, labels=[0, 1])
df_cm = pd.DataFrame(cm, index = [i for i in ["No","Yes"]],
                         columns = [i for i in ["No","Yes"]])
plt.figure(figsize = (7,7))
sns.heatmap(df_cm, annot=True ,fmt='g');

trn_sc= 94.12 %
tst_sc= 84.75 %
rcl_sc= 92.5 %
prc_sc= 86.05 %
roc_sc= 80.46 %

the model scored high in the Accuracy, very high in Recall(low False negative PD cases(FN=6))
